node.title: Elderly couple rescued amid 5,000 calls for help as floods worsen in NSW
node.alt: brick house flooded by brown water
node.description: Emergency crews rescue 13 people in 24 hours as authorities warn swollen rivers will continue to rise in flood-stricken areas of NSW, despite rain easing off.
node.content:
["The State Emergency Service has received nearly 5,000\u00a0requests for assistance in the past 24 hours from flood-affected areas in New South Wales.", "Major flood warnings remain in place for parts of the Namoi and Macquarie rivers in the state's north and the Lachlan River in the central west.", "SES spokeswoman\u00a0Vanessa Hutchinson said\u00a0although rainfall had\u00a0eased, a large volume\u00a0of water was\u00a0yet to work\u00a0its way downstream.", "She said\u00a0there had\u00a0been 13 flood rescues in the last 24 hours across the state, including the overnight rescue of an elderly couple in Gunnedah.", "\"We've had a number of people isolated with the floodwater and some of them are unable to leave their homes, as was the case with this couple, she said.", "\"And the SES went in and helped them to evacuate from that area and took them to a safe place.\"", "
Gunnedah residents evacuated
", "The Namoi River is continuing to flood the state's north west\u00a0after a weekend of significant damage and water level rises.", "", "
The RFS delivered supplied to residents isolated by floodwaters near Gunnedah.(Supplied: Courtney Evans)
", "The river peaked at Gunnedah yesterday above the major flood level at 8.61 metres, which was higher than authorities had expected.", "An evacuation centre was set up at the local basketball stadium yesterday to help residents get to higher ground.", "The Namoi River at Gunnedah currently sits at 8.47m and rising.", "SES spokesman\u00a0Dave Rankin said it had\u00a0been\u00a0a relief to see floodwaters start to\u00a0retreat, after about 100 properties were damaged by the event.", "\"From about 10 o\u2019clock last night that peak sort of hung around in Gunnedah for the best part of 12 hours yesterday, but we've certainly seen nearly 20 centimetres\u00a0of water recede from the Gunnedah community,\u201d he said.", "The SES has been airlifting supplies to homes isolated by floodwaters on either side of the Namoi, which will continue today.", "
Narrabri braces for peak
", "Downstream in Narrabri floodwaters continued to rise, and local SES crews spent the weekend sandbagging properties in preparation.", "The town is already experiencing major flooding, with a peak of 7.6m expected later tonight.", "North-west of Narrabri the town of Wee Waa is cut off by floodwaters, and Mr Rankin said they expect the major flood levels to hang around.", "\u201cWe can safely assume Wee Waa is going to be isolated for the best part of a week, so at least until Saturday we can expect road access to Wee Waa to be nonexistent,\u201d he said.", "The SES has positioned a helicopter in Narrabri specifically to help resupply the isolated community.", "Mr Rankin said emergency crews had rescued about six\u00a0people in the region, despite strong messaging to keep off flooded roads.", "\u201cDisappointingly we're still seeing some people trying to drive through that flood water,\" he said.", "\"We\u2019ve had a fair few rescues overnight along the Namoi catchment where people are still ignoring road closed signs and trying to drive through flood water\u00a0\u2014 significant floodwater, not just wheel height but quite significant deep floodwater.\"", "Mr Rankin said in Western parts of NSW the SES had\u00a0rescued close to 45 residents from floodwaters."]
